documentation.text: @title Interface for making arbitrary calls during swap
@notice propagates information about original msg.sender and executes arbitrary data
@title Clipper interface subset used in swaps

clipperSwap(address,address,address,uint.notice: Same as `clipperSwapTo` but uses `msg.sender` as recipient

params.goodUntil: Timestamp until the swap will be valid
params.inputAmount: Amount of source tokens to swap
params.outputAmount: Amount of destination tokens to receive

clipperSwapTo(address,address,address,ad.notice: Performs swap using Clipper exchange. Wraps and unwraps ETH if required. Sending non-zero `msg.value` for anything but ETH swaps is prohibited

params.goodUntil: Timestamp until the swap will be valid
params.inputAmount: Amount of source tokens to swap
params.outputAmount: Amount of destination tokens to receive
params.recipient: Address that will receive swap funds

clipperSwapToWithPermit(address,address,.notice: Same as `clipperSwapTo` but calls permit first, allowing to approve token spending and make a swap in one transaction.

params.goodUntil: Timestamp until the swap will be valid
params.inputAmount: Amount of source tokens to swap
params.outputAmount: Amount of destination tokens to receive
params.permit: Should contain valid permit that can be used in `IERC20Permit.permit` calls.
params.recipient: Address that will receive swap funds
